t-toggle-accordion-content-wrap ub-hide" id=3D"ub-content-toggle-panel-0-a5=
bdad12-9333-465b-ac04-61317406a737">

<p>To get from <tnr>-6</tnr> to <tnr>3</tnr>, we jump <tnr>3</tnr> terms.</=
p>



<p><br></p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding=3D"async" width=
=3D"108" height=3D"70" src=3D"https://thirdspacelearning.com/wp-content/upl=
oads/2021/05/Arithmetic-Sequences-Image-2.svg" alt=3D"Arithmetic Sequences =
Image 2" class=3D"wp-image-58306"></figure>



<p><br>This distance has a value of <tnr>9</tnr>. We need to divide the tot=
al distance by the number of jumps made. Here, <tnr>9 =C3=B7 3 =3D 3</tnr>.=
 This means that the common difference is <tnr>+3</tnr>.</p>

</div>
