<p id=3D"how-to-generate"></p>



<div class=3D"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-=
layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h2 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-how-to-generate-an-arithmetic-sequ=
ence">How to generate an arithmetic sequence</h2>



<p></p>



<p>In order to<strong> generate an arithmetic sequence</strong>, we need to=
 know the <strong><tnr>n</tnr><sup>th</sup> term</strong>.&nbsp;<br>The <tn=
r>n</tnr><sup>th</sup> term is the name or rule that the sequence must foll=
ow to generate an ordered list of numbers.</p>



<p></p>



<p>We can work out any number of terms of an arithmetic sequence by substit=
uting values into the <tnr>n</tnr><sup>th</sup> term.</p>



<p></p>



<p>The first term is found when <tnr>n =3D 1</tnr>, <br>the second term whe=
n <tnr>n =3D 2</tnr>, <br>the fifth term when <tnr>n =3D 5</tnr>, <br>the t=
enth term when <tnr>n =3D 10</tnr>, and so on.</p>



<p></p>



<p>This is known as the<strong> position-to-term rule</strong> as you can c=
alculate the term, given its position in the sequence.</p>



<p></p>



<ol class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li>Find the first term of the sequence by substituting <tnr>n =3D 1</tnr> =
into the <tnr>n</tnr><sup>th</sup> term.</li>



<li>Find the second term by substituting <tnr>n =3D 2</tnr> into the <tnr>n=
</tnr><sup>th</sup> term.</li>



<li>Continue to substitute values for <tnr>n</tnr> until all the required t=
erms of the sequence are calculated.</li>
</ol>



<p></p>



<p><strong>Top tip:</strong> After you have calculated the first term in th=
e sequence just keep adding the coefficient <tnr>n</tnr> to generate the se=
quence!</p>



