<p id=3D"misconceptions"></p>



<div class=3D"wp-block-columns is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-=
layout-9d6595d7 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex">
<div class=3D"wp-block-column is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow=
"><h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"h-common-misconceptions">Common misc=
onceptions</h3>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Multiplying the value for a term to get another term in the seq=
uence</strong><br>E.g.<br>Let=E2=80=99s look at the sequence <tnr> 4, 10, 1=
6, 22, 28. </tnr> <br>The third term in the sequence is <tnr> 16 </tnr>. <b=
r>The thirtieth term does not equal the third term multiplied by<tnr> 10, <=
/tnr> or <tnr> 160 </tnr> (as <tnr> 16 =C3=97 10 =3D 160 </tnr>). The thirt=
ieth term is equal to<tnr> 178</tnr>.</li>
</ul>



<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Arithmetic sequences with negative terms do not always decrease=
</strong><br>E.g.<br>The sequence <tnr> -48, -40, -32, -24, -16 </tnr> has =
a common difference of <tnr> +8. </tnr> <br>This means that even though the=
 sequence is showing negative integers rather than positive integers, it is=
 increasing.</li>
</ul>



<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Adding the constant in the <tnr>n</tnr><sup>th</sup> term inste=
ad of the common difference</strong><br>E.g.<br>The <tnr>n</tnr><sup>th</su=
p> term <tnr>3n =E2=88=92 7</tnr> will produce a sequence of numbers that h=
ave a common difference of <tnr> 3. </tnr> The misconception would occur if=
 the next term is found by subtracting <tnr> 7 </tnr> rather than adding <t=
nr> 3 </tnr>.</li>
</ul>



<p></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong><strong>Simplifying the <tnr>n</tnr><sup>th</sup> term incorrec=
tly</strong></strong><br>E.g.  <br>Incorrectly simplifying <tnr>6n + 2</tnr=
> to give <tnr>8n</tnr>.<br>This is incorrect for any value other than when=
 <tnr>n =3D 1</tnr>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>



